## Publication Figures

These static figures provide publication-style low-dimensional summaries of all retained samples after probe harmonization and normalization across runs.

### PCA

Principal component analysis highlights the dominant axes of global methylation variation across the merged cohort.

```{r pca-static}
knitr::include_graphics("results/figures/all_samples_pca.png")
report_download_link("results/tables/all_samples_pca.csv")
```

### UMAP

UMAP emphasizes local neighborhood structure and is useful for visually separating compact subgroups or mixed cohorts.

```{r umap-static}
knitr::include_graphics("results/figures/all_samples_umap.png")
report_download_link("results/tables/all_samples_umap.csv")
```

### t-SNE

t-SNE provides a complementary nonlinear embedding that can reveal local sample structure not obvious in PCA.

```{r tsne-static}
knitr::include_graphics("results/figures/all_samples_tsne.png")
report_download_link("results/tables/all_samples_tsne.csv")
```

